728 typedef enum SearchStrategy_enum {
729  IMAQ_CONSERVATIVE = 1, //Instructs the pattern matching algorithm to use the largest possible amount of information from the image at the expense of slowing down the speed of the algorithm.
730  IMAQ_BALANCED = 2, //Instructs the pattern matching algorithm to balance the amount of information from the image it uses with the speed of the algorithm.
731  IMAQ_AGGRESSIVE = 3, //Instructs the pattern matching algorithm to use a lower amount of information from the image, which allows the algorithm to run quickly but at the expense of accuracy.
732  IMAQ_VERY_AGGRESSIVE = 4, //Instructs the pattern matching algorithm to use the smallest possible amount of information from the image, which allows the algorithm to run at the highest speed possible but at the expense of accuracy.
733  IMAQ_SEARCH_STRATEGY_SIZE_GUARD = 0xFFFFFFFF
734 } SearchStrategy;
735 
736 typedef enum MeterArcMode_enum {
737  IMAQ_METER_ARC_ROI = 0, //The function uses the roi parameter and ignores the base, start, and end parameters.
738  IMAQ_METER_ARC_POINTS = 1, //The function uses the base,start, and end parameters and ignores the roi parameter.
739  IMAQ_METER_ARC_MODE_SIZE_GUARD = 0xFFFFFFFF
740 } MeterArcMode;
741 
742 typedef enum MorphologyMethod_enum {
743  IMAQ_AUTOM = 0, //The function uses a transformation that generates simpler particles that contain fewer details.
744  IMAQ_CLOSE = 1, //The function uses a transformation that fills tiny holes and smooths boundaries.
745  IMAQ_DILATE = 2, //The function uses a transformation that eliminates tiny holes isolated in particles and expands the contour of the particles according to the template defined by the structuring element.
746  IMAQ_ERODE = 3, //The function uses a transformation that eliminates pixels isolated in the background and erodes the contour of particles according to the template defined by the structuring element.
747  IMAQ_GRADIENT = 4, //The function uses a transformation that leaves only the pixels that would be added by the dilation process or eliminated by the erosion process.
748  IMAQ_GRADIENTOUT = 5, //The function uses a transformation that leaves only the pixels that would be added by the dilation process.
749  IMAQ_GRADIENTIN = 6, //The function uses a transformation that leaves only the pixels that would be eliminated by the erosion process.
750  IMAQ_HITMISS = 7, //The function uses a transformation that extracts each pixel located in a neighborhood exactly matching the template defined by the structuring element.
751  IMAQ_OPEN = 8, //The function uses a transformation that removes small particles and smooths boundaries.
752  IMAQ_PCLOSE = 9, //The function uses a transformation that fills tiny holes and smooths the inner contour of particles according to the template defined by the structuring element.
753  IMAQ_POPEN = 10, //The function uses a transformation that removes small particles and smooths the contour of particles according to the template defined by the structuring element.
754  IMAQ_THICK = 11, //The function uses a transformation that adds to an image those pixels located in a neighborhood that matches a template specified by the structuring element.
755  IMAQ_THIN = 12, //The function uses a transformation that eliminates pixels that are located in a neighborhood matching a template specified by the structuring element.
756  IMAQ_MORPHOLOGY_METHOD_SIZE_GUARD = 0xFFFFFFFF
757 } MorphologyMethod;
758

765 typedef enum OutlineMethod_enum {

771  IMAQ_EDGE_SOBEL = 5, //The function uses a method that extracts the outer contours of objects.
772  IMAQ_OUTLINE_METHOD_SIZE_GUARD = 0xFFFFFFFF
